Heat oven to 375 degrees F. Remove and unfold crusts from package. Cut out 12 circles from each crust, using 2 1/2-inch round cutter. Press each circle in bottom and up side of ungreased miniature muffin cup. Melt butter in 10-inch skillet. Cook onion in butter 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly, until tender. Stir together onion and remaining ingredients except spinach in small bowl; beat well. Stir in spinach. Divide mixture evenly among crust-lined cups. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until puffed and golden brown. Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes. Loosen and remove quiches from pan with tip of knife. Serve warm or cool. Store in refrigerator.